<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,506,1304]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1184,1208]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was previously known from the female 
<typeStatus box="[915,1011,1184,1207]" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">holotype</typeStatus>
, which is in somewhat poor condition. The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[286,399,1217,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Leioproctus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosellae">
<emphasis box="[286,399,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="78">L. rosellae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
agrees in most characters with those of the female, except in the usual secondary sexual features, the shorter, sparser body pubescence and the integument with coarser and denser punctures, particularly on head and metasomal terga.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
